    "description": "An R package to assess nonverbal synchronization in motion energy analysis time-series.\n\nThe goal of rMEA is to provide a suite of tools useful to read, visualize and export bivariate Motion Energy time-series. Lagged synchrony between subjects can be analyzed through windowed cross-correlation. Surrogate data generation allows an estimation of pseudosynchrony that helps to estimate the effect size of the observed synchronization.",
